{
  "text": "Since (B 3 , g), g ∈ M has no conjugate points, the distance function r(z, z ) ∈ C ∞ (B 3 ×B 3 \\Diag), where Diag = {(z, z ) ∈ B 3 × B 3 : z = z }. We establish some properties of the distance function to be used in the parametrix construction of Section 3. By abuse of notations, we use C ω (M ) to denote both real analytic functions and real analytic two forms on a real analytic manifold M . For functions f (z, z ) defined on the product space M × M , we say f ∈ C ω (M × M ) if f is separately real analytic in z, z . Note there is a difference between jointly real analyticity and separately real analyticity, see Section 4.3 of [CITATION_1] . For our purpose, it is sufficient to consider separately real analytic functions.",
